HEADWORD: Salubrity
<hw>Sa*lu"bri*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salubritas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>salubrit⟦eacute⟧</ets> See
<er>Salubrious</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being salubrious;
favorableness to the preservation of health; salubriousness;
wholesomeness; healthfulness; <as>as, the <ex>salubrity</ex> of the air,
of a country, or a climate</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A sweet, dry smell of
<xex>salubrity</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>G. W. Cable.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

